A4.text: Ella Jane Fitzgerald (April 25, 1917 – June 15, 1996) was an American singer, songwriter and composer, sometimes referred to as the 'First Lady of Song', 'Queen of Jazz', and 'Lady Ella'.

A5.text: Ella Fitzgerald was born on April 25, 1917, in Newport News, Virginia.

A6.text: Billie Holiday (born Eleanora Fagan; April 7, 1915 – July 17, 1959) was an American jazz and swing music singer.
